overview: Vince Lane is an experienced Graphic Designer, always working to stay one step ahead of what’s hot in the design industry. At the age of 23, he’s way ahead of the game. He’s lead the design direction on a number of large web development projects while working for Little Green Cube, a web development firm in Chicago. He currently works as a designer for the Chicago Free Press, contributing to a weekly newspaper, website design, and a monthly magazine published by the paper. In addition, he successfully runs a small freelance design business of his own, and has worked with some large clients, including McGrath Lexus.
